<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Image and Text Side by Side</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet"
        href="styles.css">
</head>
    <style>
        .container {
            display: flex; /* Flexbow layout */
            align-items: center; /* Align items vertically */
            justify-content: space-between; /* space between the image and text */
            width: 80%;
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 20px auto; /* center the container horizontally */
            padding: 20;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .image {
            flex: 1; /* adjusts image size */
            max-width: 50%; /* prevents the image from exceeding half the container */
            margin-right: 20px;
        }

        .image img {
            width: 100%; /* makes the image responsive */
            height: auto; /* maintains aspect ratio */
            border-radius: 8px; /* optional: rounded corners for the image */
        }

        .text {
            flex: 2; /*adjusts text size relative to the imge */
        }

        .test h1 {
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        .text p {
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="image">
            <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.HLu99uATREB41fqx50grSAAAAA?w=175&h=176&c=7&r=0&o=5&dpr=1.5&pid=1.7" alt="fingers image">
        </div>
        <div class="text">
            <h1>Title Goes Here</h1>
            <p>This is some text on the right side of the container. You can add as much text as you need, and it will stay neatly aligned next to the image.</p>
            <p>Feel free to style this content further as needed for your layout.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>